   <text>
      <body>
         <pb facs="page_image1" n="1"/>
         <div>
            <ab>
               <lb/>THE  CHILDREN'S
               <lb/>MORAL
               <lb/>ALPHABET
            </ab>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image2" n="2"/>

         <pb facs="page_image3" n="3"/>
         <div>
            <ab>
               <lb/>THE  CHILDREN'S
               <lb/>MORAL
               <lb/>ALPHABET
            </ab>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image4" n="4"/>
         <pb facs="page_image5" n="5"/>
         <div>
            <ab>
               <lb />Having observed what utter nonsense is put into the mouths of children, and € the firm hold which it takes on their memories, (I refer to “A was an Archer that shot at a frog, &amp;c.,) I have ventured to compose, in simple rhyme, what I will call “The Children’s Moral Alphabet," with the hope that it may as easily, and as permanently, lodge in the mind a few grains of truth which shall germinate, and even bear some fruit, in the future.
               <lb />With this view, I submit it to the juvenile public, with my best wishes for their progress in all that is good and true. At the same time apologising for here and there giving a hint to the elder folk.
               <lb />OCTOGENARIAN
               <lb />Kettering, July, 1879.
            </ab>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image6" n="6"/>
         <pb facs="page_image7" n="7"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag1" ana="A">
            <head>A</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for the Ass: this burden he bore,—</l>
               <l>A hag of good meal from the water-mill store;</l>
               <l>Then should he be beaten ’cause slowly he trod ?</l>
               <l>No! Neddy and meal are both creatures of God.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image8" n="8"/>
         <pb facs="page_image9" n="9"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag2" ana="B">
            <head>B</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for Bible, the book of all truth,</l>
               <l>Which guides to the Saviour both old age and youth;</l>
               <l>Dear England, old England, thy children are blest,</l>
               <l>Not one need there he of this Book unpossessed.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
            <pb facs="page_image10" n="10"/>
            <pb facs="page_image11" n="11"/>
            <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag3" ana="C">
               <head>C</head>
               <lg>
                  <l>Stands for Coat, that keeps me so warm,</l>
                  <l>When foot-deep in snow I am plodding the farm;</l>
                  <l>I shepherd the sheep, and think it’s their wool</l>
                  <l>That makes all the coats of the boys in our school.</l>
               </lg>
            </div>
            <pb facs="page_image12" n="12"/>
            <pb facs="page_image13" n="13"/>
            <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag4" ana="D">
               <head>D</head>
               <lg>
                  <l>Stands for Drunkard—oh, shocking the sight!</l>
                  <l>Let me ne'er be found in such wretched plight:</l>
                  <l>A grief to my parents, offensive to God-</l>
                  <l>Save me, 0 save me, from that downward road!</l>
               </lg>
            </div>
         <pb facs="page_image14" n="14"/>
         <pb facs="page_image15" n="15"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag5" ana="E">
            <head>E</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for Eagle, who soars as he flies,</l>
               <l>Upwards, still upwards, he mounts to the skies;</l>
               <l>While he who hates learning, an Idler lies down,</l>
               <l>Content to he always an ignorant clown,</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image16" n="16"/>
         <pb facs="page_image17" n="17"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag6" ana="F">
            <head>F</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for a Fool, an Atheist he;</l>
               <l>At the great judgment-day, oh, where will he be?</l>
               <l>Speechless, confounded, with agonized heart,</l>
               <l>Awaiting his sentence—Depart ye, depart!</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image18" n="18"/>
         <pb facs="page_image19" n="19"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag7" ana="G">
            <head>G</head>
            <lg>
               <l>G Stands for Goliath, six cubits in height,</l>
               <l>In armour complete equipped for the light;</l>
               <l>I While cursing young David, with boastful disdain,</l>
               <l>Forth flew the missile: the Giant was slain.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image20" n="20"/>
         <pb facs="page_image21" n="21"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag8" ana="H">
            <head>H</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for Home, so sweet and so comely,</l>
               <l>For love makes it sweet, be it ever so I homely;</l>
               <l>Then brothers and sisters pray love one another,</l>
               <l>Joy will it bring to both Father and Mother.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image22" n="22"/>
         <pb facs="page_image23" n="23"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag9" ana="I">
            <head>I</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for Ink, let all try to use it,</l>
               <l>But never take pen whereby to abuse it;</l>
               <l>For it, like the tongue, true friendships may sever,</l>
               <l>To unite again—when? the time may come never.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image24" n="24"/>
         <pb facs="page_image25" n="25"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag10" ana="J">
            <head>J</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for the Judge, who solemnly sits</l>
               <l>To lay down the law that condemns or acquits;</l>
               <l>While twelve honest men take oath on the spot,</l>
               <l>To give a true verdict, of guilty or not.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image26" n="26"/>
         <pb facs="page_image27" n="27"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag11" ana="K">
            <head>K</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for the King, who sits on the Throne;</l>
               <l>He speaks of “ mj people," but we're not his own:</l>
               <l>Our grand Constitution, I’m proud to relate,</l>
               <l>Is King, Lords, and Commons,—we call it the State,</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image28" n="28"/>
         <pb facs="page_image29" n="29"/>
         
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag12" ana="L">
            <head>L</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for lamb, what a time honoured name!</l>
               <l>Since Jesus, the Lord, is well known by the same;</l>
               <l>For lo! on the Cross He gave up His breath,</l>
               <l>To save a lost world from sin and from death.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image30" n="30"/>
         <pb facs="page_image31" n="31"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag13" ana="M">
            <head>M</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for Mother, fair emblem of love,</l>
               <l>Who nursed me, and fed me, and called me her dove:</l>
               <l>what can I render such love and affection</l>
               <l>n weakness and age? ij kindest protection.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image32" n="32"/>
         <pb facs="page_image33" n="33"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag14" ana="N">
            <head>N</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for Neighbour, oh, what says the lord ?</l>
               <l>“Love him as yourself," it stands on record ;</l>
               <l>And should he offend you, to seven times even,</l>
               <l>Your love must forgive to seventy times seven.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image34" n="34"/>
         <pb facs="page_image35" n="35"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag15" ana="O">
            <head>O</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for Oyster, with rough-coated shell;</l>
               <l>When the morsel you've tasted, examine it well;</l>
               <l>Judge no man in haste, it will not be kind,</l>
               <l>The outside is nothing: the pearl is the mind.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image36" n="36"/>
         <pb facs="page_image37" n="37"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag16" ana="P">
            <head>P</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for Peter, sad storj to tell,—</l>
               <l>He trusted in self: you know how he fell; </l>
               <l>But was kindly restored by a glance of the eye</l>
               <l>From Jesus, his Saviour, lest Peter should die.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image38" n="38"/>
         <pb facs="page_image39" n="39"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag17" ana="Q">
            <head>Q</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for Quick: it’s no nse delaying;</l>
               <l>Time flies apace, and never means staying;</l>
               <l>So ponder the thought, that man, like a flower,</l>
               <l>Though blooming with health, is cut down in an hour,</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image40" n="40"/>
         <pb facs="page_image41" n="41"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag18" ana="R">
            <head>R</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for a Rose, the garden’s fair queen;</l>
               <l>How lovely the pink, how charming the green!</l>
               <l>Not less the fair maiden adds grace to her beauty,</l>
               <l>When love and affection give impulse to duty.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image42" n="42"/>
         <pb facs="page_image43" n="43"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag19" ana="S">
            <head>S</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for the Sun, he sends out his rays,</l>
               <l>He lights np the earth, her grandeur displays;</l>
               <l>The air fills with music from coppice and wood,</l>
               <l>Proclaiming in chorus the goodness of God.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image44" n="44"/>
         <pb facs="page_image45" n="45"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag20" ana="T">
            <head>T</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for Tiger, whose nature is cruel,</l>
               <l>And men are no better who fight in a duel:</l>
               <l>Nor should Christian nations partake the disgrace</l>
               <l>Of sanctioning war, to destroy their own race.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image46" n="46"/>
         <pb facs="page_image47" n="47"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag21" ana="U">
            <head>U</head>
            <lg>
               <l>Stands for "Ursus," in English, the Bear;</l>
               <l>An ugly old fellow, so pray you beware!</l>
               <l>A brute may be bearish, but men should know better;</l>
               <l>Youth should be kind, and polite to the letter.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image48" n="48"/>
         <pb facs="page_image49" n="49"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag22" ana="V">
            <head>V</head>
            <lg>
               <l>H, Holy Father, no culture but Thine,</l>
               <l>Can make me a branch of Christ, the true Vine;</l>
               <l>Thy pruning alone, by faith and by prayer,</l>
               <l>Can make the good fruit in rich clusters appear.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         
         <pb facs="page_image50" n="50"/>
         <pb facs="page_image51" n="51"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag23" ana="W">
            <head>W</head>
            <lg>
               <l>WEATHERCOCK, Weathercock, turned by the wind,</l>
               <l>Type of the man who knows not his own mind;</l>
               <l>While valiant for truth, he stands like a tower,</l>
               <l>His girdle is strength, his armour is power.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image52" n="52"/>
         <pb facs="page_image53" n="53"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag24" ana="X">
            <head>X</head>
            <lg>
               <l>NOT a word in our language begins with an X,</l>
               <l>But there he sits striding, poor Rhymer to vex;</l>
               <l>Be patient, poor Rhymer, don’t trouble your head,</l>
               <l>But close your long ditty with— X, Y and Z</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image54" n="54"/>
         <div type="alpha-group" xml:id="ag25" ana="XYZ">
            <head>XYZ</head>
            <lg>
               <l>BUT oh, Mr. Rhymer, you spoke of politeness:</l>
               <l>We ask, Is it right, by dint of adroitness,</l>
               <l>That we should he left as though we were dead ?</l>
               <l>We rank with our fellows as X, Y, and Z.</l>
               <l>So pray, aged Sir, our minds to compose,</l>
               <l>dive us a last word, in rhyme or in prose.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <pb facs="page_image55" n="55"/>
         <pb facs="page_image56" n="56"/>
